## Docker Deployment

```bash
# Development
docker compose up --build -d
curl http://localhost:8000/health

# Production (PostgreSQL)
cp .env.example .env          # Edit with production values
export POSTGRES_PASSWORD=$(openssl rand -hex 16)
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up --build -d
```

The production stack includes PostgreSQL 16, resource limits, and `no-new-privileges` security. The Dockerfile runs as a non-root `appuser`.

> For full deployment instructions including Nginx, systemd, TLS, and scaling, see [DEPLOYMENT.md](../DEPLOYMENT.md).

## Troubleshooting

| Issue                                   | Solution                                                                                      |
| --------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `SECRET_KEY is using the default value` | Set `SECRET_KEY` env var (required in production: `ENV=production`)                           |
| `RuntimeError: SECRET_KEY must be set`  | Production mode enforces a real secret key (≥ 32 chars, high entropy)                         |
| CORS errors                             | Add frontend URL to `ALLOWED_ORIGINS`                                                         |
| 429 Too Many Requests                   | Adjust `RATE_LIMIT_AUTH` / `RATE_LIMIT_DEFAULT`                                               |
| Frontend can't reach backend            | Ensure backend is on port 8000, check Next.js rewrites                                        |
| SQLite locked under load                | Switch `DATABASE_URL` to PostgreSQL                                                           |
| Bittensor timeout                       | Check wallet registration and increase `BT_QUERY_TIMEOUT`                                     |
| Tests fail with 429                     | Rate limiter state accumulates across test files — autouse fixture in `conftest.py` clears it |

